<https://admin.dataportal.se/store/818/resource/2d892f190b55335a8e6d64a2384d3489> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/language> <http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/language/ENG>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/publisher> <http://dataportal.se/organisation/SE2021002817>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "Red Chromatic Index (RCI) also known as Red Chromatic Coordinate (RCC) is a measure of the redness of vegetation. It is calculated from daily averaged RGB (Red, Green, Blue) composites values of digital images captured by PhenoCams.\nRöbäcksdalen Field Research Station (2022). Phenocam - Red Chromatic Coordinates (RCC) Composite Image Mean Values from Röbäcksdalen Research Area, Mast 4m Phenocam 02, 2020-03-30–2020-10-04 [Data set]. Swedish Infrastructure for Ecosystem Science (SITES). https://hdl.handle.net/11676.1/YputupjcEM4j599HZqfGzpBf"@en;
